<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-28T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-28T15:00:00-05:00" n="155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">345.1163/86b: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Commissioner in India</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-28T15:00:00-05:00">October 28, 1941—3
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>4. With reference to the Department’s September 16, 10 p.m., and
                                October 16, 8 p.m.,<note n="56" xml:id="d155fn56">Latter not
                                    printed.</note> to Calcutta, please report by telegraph
                                immediately on action taken with respect to alleged refusal of
                                Government of India to grant visas to Lutheran missionaries.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>